We want to mention once again that each chapter will be unique in its ability for Edenhorde holders to interact with.

The expansion NFTs that Edenhorde holders will be able to claim will not currently have utility outside of the story, and will only be usable or claimable within limited windows between episodes (usually 10 - 14 days).

These NFTs are freely transferable and exchangeable on the OpenSea marketplace. We will post the official collection link on OpenSea once it‚Äôs live.

Any collections released before the 14th of February are false and should be reported.

The Edenhorde expansions NFTs are three ERC1155 tokens. This enables gas efficient claiming for multiple items.

You will be able to claim your chosen NFTs on Monday the 14th of March.

üìú Who‚Äôs going to win the 2022 UEFA Champions League?

(@plantmeatree) Hi Andy! What‚Äôs one thing you could tell your younger self that could pivot where you are now in a positive way?

I wish I knew how much my time was worth and what to charge for my work. I am still struggling to figure this out...

(@vakkuda) Are there any Easter eggs from your previous works in Edenhorde?

Haha, I can't think of any off the top of my head, but maybe unintentionally.

(@NFThashler) What was the most fun tribe to design and why was it Babbumatta?

Trying to trick me, eh. They were all pretty fun to do. each had great aspects to them.

But the one that surprised me the most were the Larricks

(@Digital4ddict) What was your experience like working with the team? Is it different from a studio production?

They let me do what I want, and pursue ideas and whims that I came up.

The only other job I've had that gave me that much freedom was early on in Adventure Time

(@JovianNodes) Did you ever envision sub-communities forming around single traits of your artwork?

No, i had no idea that would happen. Edenhorde is my first experience diving into NFT's in general, so all of this is new to me...

üé® What do you think about Edenhorde's finished result?

I'm extremely happy with how things turned out. It took a bit longer than expected to create the artwork but I think we ended up with something I feel is really interesting and innovative.

üé® Which author had the greatest impact on you growing up?

It's tough to say. Books maybe Tolkien or Roald Dahl. Comics wise, Chris Clairmont's X-men run, Katsuhiro Otomo, Bill Watterson.

üé® What does a really great day look like for you?

I don't know. Since the pandemics hit everything has kinda blended into one another. I guess at the moment a great day is a real day off where I'm just relaxing and enjoying time with loved ones.

Ultimately, the point of this thread is to say that rarity is subjective. 

We love our tribes from top to bottom and we hope you will too. üî±
Rarity (currently) has no impact on future utility for Edenhorde NFT holders including during the narrative arc.

With that in mind, any rarity ranking tools you use today, please use as a guide rather than a single source of truth. 

We will be launching a our own ranking tool in the near future with filters for tribes.

What we‚Äôre not sure about is how any of this impacts perceived value. Will the rarest Babbumatta be perceived at a higher value than a lower ranked Oru? Ultimately you will decide and we‚Äôre very excited to see how this plays out.
This will ideally mean a more diverse top 10% for most rankings, with Babbumatta, Gadirans and Larriks making lots of appearances.

However, most rarity ranking tools do not use ‚Äòstatistical rarity‚Äô, but will instead calculate a rarity score, which will take into account individually rare NFTs that may belong to a more populous tribe.

Using ‚Äòstatistical rarity‚Äô, Oru‚Äôs will appear in the top 880 of the collection in terms of ranking. 

‚ÄòStatistical rarity‚Äô is where, as an example, an NFT has 2 traits with 1 trait at 10% and the other trait at 50%, the ‚Äòstatistical rarity‚Äô for that NFT would be (10% * 50%) = 5%.

TRAITS: 

Edenhorde does not have cross-tribe traits. 

All traits are visually unique to a tribe. 

This impacts ‚Äòstatistical rarity‚Äô as tribes play a large role in the frequency of traits in the entire collection.

Firstly, your chances of owning a specific tribe at reveal (assuming one NFT): 

üçÉBabbumatta: 32% 
üë¶Larriks: 30% 
üè∞Gadirans: 28% 
ü§ñOru: 10%

ON RANKING RARITY: 

Rarity in Edenhorde is a bit different from most projects. 

The tribe system is such an integral part to how the collection is structured that this does have an impact on how rarity can be ranked.
